content.problemStatement:
Chef found a rooted tree with NNN nodes. The nodes are labeled from 111 to NNN. Node with label 111 was marked as the root.

RRR is the adjacency list representing the tree, which includes only children, but not the parent of every node. Denote K(i)K(i)K(i) as the number of children of the ithi^{th}ith node. Denote R(i,j)R(i, j)R(i,j) as the jthj^{th}jth child of the ithi^{th}ith node (0‚â§j&lt;K(i)0 \leq j &lt; K(i)0‚â§j&lt;K(i)).

Chef also found the piece of code lying below the tree.

`void dfs(v, iter) {
  if (visit[v] == 0)
    visit[v] = iter;
  if (K(v) != 0) {
    special_child = R(v, F(v));
    dfs(special_child, iter);
    F(v) = (F(v) + 1) % K(v);
  }
}

initialize F(i) = 0;
initialize visit[i] = 0;
done = false;
iter = 0;

while (!done) {
  iter = iter + 1;
  dfs(1, iter);
  done = true;
  for (i = 1; i &lt;= N; ++i)
    if (visit[i] == 0)
      done = false;
}
`Chef is really excited to see this code and wants to know what is the value of the visitvisitvisit array once this code is executed.

Since the values of the array can be large, print all the integers mod‚Äâ‚Äâ109+7\mod 10^9+7mod109+7.


Input Format

First line will contain TTT, the number of test cases. Then the test cases follow.
The first line of each test case contains a single integer NNN, the number of nodes in the tree.
NNN lines follow.
The first integer on the ithi^{th}ith line denotes K(i)K(i)K(i), the number of children of node iii. K(i)K(i)K(i) integers follow, the jthj^{th}jth of which denotes R(i,j)R(i, j)R(i,j).


Output Format
For each test case, output in a single line NNN space-separated integers.
